        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:11PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1211 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Davis, or over Beckwourth. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beckwourth, Grizzly Campground, and Lake Davis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
